  "text": "Millimeter-wave (mm-wave) wireless communication systems are attracting growing interests. With the continuous scaling of CMOS processes, it is now possible to design circuits operating in millimeter-wave frequency range using silicon technology. Several applications either exist or are envisioned for mm-wave frequencies among which, are broadband multi-Gbps data communication, automotive radar, medical & security imagining and chip-to-chip communication [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] .",
